com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.mem
Interface Fetch

public interface Fetch

The Fetch interface defines the constants used to define what parts of the native memory layout of a native object tree must be read.

Author:
jmarranz
See Also:
NativeManager.fetch(Object,int)

Field Detail

NONE

static final int NONE
Constant used to specify that native memory is not read.

See Also:
UnFetch.NONE, Constant Field Values

FAST

static final int FAST
Constant used to specify that a fast fetch must be performed.

Only field members with primitive types, “can be native” class types and the address of fields with native capable class types “by pointer”, are fetched. The referenced native object of a field with a native capable class type declared “by pointer”, is not fetched itself, only the object’s address with the related pointer in the container’s native memory is fetched.

See Also:
UnFetch.FAST, Constant Field Values

EMBEDDED

static final int EMBEDDED
Constant used to specify that embedded native member objects must be fetched too.

The native objects referenced by fields with native capable class types declared “by value” (native embedded objects) are fetched, themselves, with the related native memory too.

See Also:
UnFetch.EMBEDDED, Constant Field Values

DEEP

static final int DEEP
Constant used to specify that a deep fetch must be performed.

All members of the native object, including linked native objects, must be fetched recursively.

See Also:
UnFetch.DEEP, Constant Field Values
